[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ceredigion crash victim named as Stephen Joseph Cuddy

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man killed in a lorry crash in Ceredigion has been named as Stephen Joseph Cuddy.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 42 year old died near Devil's Bridge when a bin lorry crashed on the B4574 at 10:50 BST on Saturday.
In a statement, Mr Cuddy's family described him as a "lovely, honest, caring son, brother and uncle".
A 64-year-old man also involved in the crash was airlifted to Morriston Hospital in Swansea but police say his condition is not life threatening.
Mr Cuddy's family added: "Stephen was a keen motorcyclist who loved the countryside and loved Wales."
Dyfed-Powys Police is appealing for witnesses.
